manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: BLANBOK+ MFi Certified Memory Stick - Enables easy data sharing among different devices. The BLANBOK+ photo stick has versatile interfaces (lightning, Type C, and USB A with an adapter), ensuring compatibility with iPhone, iPad, OTG Android, PC, and devices with standard USB ports. This simplifies data transfer between devices for easy sharing.Compact and Portable: The iPhone storage flash drive measures just 2.5 * 0.5 * 0.3 inches, making it small, exquisite, and easy to carry wherever you go.

Sleek and Durable Metal Casing This type c flash drive has a sleek and stylish metal casing, making it perfect for on-the-go use. Its durability ensures maximum protection for the internal chips and data. The lightweight design allows for easy portability, whether it's in a pocket, on a keychain, or in a bag. It's perfect for everyday use, work, or travel. Dual Chip Design The dual-chip design of the usb c thumb drive allows for simultaneous reading and writing of data, improving transfer speed. Compared to traditional single-chip designs, the dual-chip design allows for faster transfer of large amounts of data and enhances the durability of the pendrive. One-Click Backup With BLANBOK+ usb drive 128gb, you can easily backup and manage files without relying on iTunes. Using our mobile app, you can conveniently manage files, phone book, photos, and videos on your phone and quickly backup them to mini flash drive, saving storage space on your phone. Additionally, you can share files on the usb thumb drives and store your captured videos, photos, or favorite movies on the 128GB flash drive for direct viewing.

High Compatibility The usb c storage flash drive supports the read and storage of various file formats, including documents, photos, videos, and audio, which can be easily stored and backed up on the USB drive. It supports the following systems - iOS 7.1.2 or higher versions, MacOS, Windows, and Android. Protect File Privacy The BLANBOK+ iPhone photo transfer stick includes a dedicated password and Touch ID feature for encrypting file information within the app. Setting a password or utilizing Touch ID helps safeguard your private files from theft or leaks. More Storage Space for Your iPhone Expand storage effortlessly: With a memory stick for iphone, you can easily store files externally and free up space on your phone. Whether it's photos, videos, documents, or music, you can conveniently store and access them anytime. Enjoy a lighter phone and more freedom in your life.

Remarks: 1.To use the encrypted flash drive on your iPhone or iPad, you need to download the app "BLANBOK+" from the App Store. In case the iphone storage flash drive is not recognized by your phone, uninstall the "BLANBOK+" app, restart your phone, and manually download the app again from the App Store. 2.If you have previously backed up files on iCloud, you will need to download the files to your phone or iPad from iCloud and then copy them to the USB flash drive. 3.The usb storage flash drive is only compatible for Android phones that have the OTG function. You can find the external USB storage in the "File Manager" app on your phone. If your phone doesn't work, you need to open the phone settings to enable the OTG connection. Please Note: 1.Media files downloaded from iTunes or other third-party applications cannot be transferred or viewed due to digital rights management protection. 2.For small-capacity lightning flash drives that have better compatibility, the preferred format is FAT32. For large-capacity USB flash drives, it is recommended to use exFAT format. If the photo storage device is unable to transfer files, you can convert the format from FAT32 to exFAT by formatting. However, remember to save the files before formatting to prevent data loss. 3.After using the photo stick, ensure that you turn off any apps related to the iphone thumb drive and gently unplug the usb jump drive to prevent any damage to the files stored on it.

reviews.reviewText: I bought this for my daughter for Christmas. She struggles with storage on her iPhone because she takes so many pictures. She said this flash drive is by far the best gift she received. It was easy to use and will solve her storage problem.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Why anyone would give this less than a 5 Star review is beyond me.
reviews.reviewText: I always worried about losing my pictures stored on my iPhone and iPad and now that worry is over. As a man, I don't read instructions. I figured this device out without instructions in roughly ten minutes. Plug it into your phone of iPad and figure it out. Alternatively, you could read the instructions, I guess.I bought two Sandisk disk drives, downloaded all my pictures and videos from my phone onto this little drive, plugged the new drive into my Mac and transferred all of those 1700+ pictures and videos onto the Sandisk drives and I'm all set. I love it! I'm very glad I bought it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Horrible App - No File Backup And Limited to Photo/Video Album Transfers
reviews.reviewText: The app has a nice misguided GUI, that looks good but functions poorly.The app does not support file backup (Backup function only backs up contacts).The app provides limited access to photo albums and videos for copying to the USB that is far more cumbersome than other similar products. The external storage function gives statistics and allows adding files from albums in internal storage.The internal storage function of the App gives statistics, but does not allow access to files in internal storage.Physically the USB is well constructed, but the lighting connection has a bulky shoulder that prevents inserting with any protective covers installed. The USB drive well as a USB A drive, but the App makes the other two ports limited in use.There is a reason the BlanBok+ App has a very poor rating and equally poor reviews in the App Store!

reviews.reviewText: Yes, this is not a regular flash drive.
